00:19:45,475 --> 00:19:46,935
I applied for training abroad.

254
00:19:48,437 --> 00:19:49,563
If I get accepted,

255
00:19:51,064 --> 00:19:52,524
I'm going to take a leave of absence.

256
00:19:55,485 --> 00:19:56,528
You're

257
00:19:57,070 --> 00:19:59,656
in charge of my evaluations,

258
00:20:00,490 --> 00:20:02,201
so I thought you should know.

259
00:20:06,455 --> 00:20:07,873
The division is too much for me.

260
00:20:11,543 --> 00:20:13,587
For someone like you,

261
00:20:14,838 --> 00:20:16,840
my lack of sense of duty

262
00:20:18,217 --> 00:20:19,885
might seem baffling.

263
00:20:22,596 --> 00:20:24,848
However,
I don't think I can continue working here.

264
00:20:26,725 --> 00:20:28,685
Another division seems scary too.

265
00:20:34,024 --> 00:20:35,150
After I go abroad,

266
00:20:35,901 --> 00:20:38,237
-I'm considering a safer position--
-Okay.

267
00:20:40,697 --> 00:20:41,949
Do it.

268
00:20:42,908 --> 00:20:44,576
Just do as you planned.
What's the problem?

269
00:21:03,303 --> 00:21:05,722
<i>-When I repeated your name
-When I repeated your name</i>

270
00:21:05,806 --> 00:21:10,560
<i>-Your burning voice ringing in my ears
-Your burning voice ringing in my ears</i>

271
00:21:10,644 --> 00:21:13,689
<i>-That was my salvation
-That was my salvation</i>

272
00:21:13,772 --> 00:21:18,402
<i>-If I can run through the dry sky
-If I can run through the dry sky</i>

273
00:21:18,485 --> 00:21:21,822
<i>-Straight to your embrace
-Straight to your embrace</i>

274
00:21:21,905 --> 00:21:28,662
<i>-I wouldn't mind breaking any bones
-I wouldn't mind breaking any bones</i>

275
00:21:28,745 --> 00:21:33,917
<i>-Even if I fly too close to the sun
-Even if I fly too close to the sun</i>

276
00:21:34,501 --> 00:21:39,131
<i>-Even if both my legs melt
-Even if both my legs melt</i>

277
00:21:56,189 --> 00:21:58,567
I was proud of my mentor today.

278
00:21:59,192 --> 00:22:01,445
He didn't cry and had a lot of fun.

279
00:22:01,987 --> 00:22:03,280
Why would I cry?

280
00:22:05,615 --> 00:22:08,660
I'm not just saying this, you know.

281
00:22:11,663 --> 00:22:14,624
I'm happy that

282
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:17,336
I'm finally off the job.

283
00:22:18,086 --> 00:22:19,338
I really am.

284
00:22:22,716 --> 00:22:23,759
I feel bad for you.

285
00:22:25,135 --> 00:22:26,178
You and

286
00:22:26,845 --> 00:22:28,138
Yang-chon both.

287
00:22:29,431 --> 00:22:30,640
I fell bad that

288
00:22:31,433 --> 00:22:32,976
you guys are still cops.

289
00:22:35,145 --> 00:22:37,481
Thanks for your heartfelt words.

290
00:22:40,859 --> 00:22:43,528
Lieutenant, don't forget to keep in touch.

291
00:22:44,863 --> 00:22:45,781
I'm not going to.

292
00:22:46,782 --> 00:22:50,577
I'm sick and tired of
everything related to the job.

293
00:22:51,578 --> 00:22:53,747
You should quit too.

294
00:22:54,539 --> 00:22:56,041
Starting today,

295
00:22:56,750 --> 00:22:59,628
I won't even pee
in the direction of our division.

296
00:22:59,878 --> 00:23:00,921
I really won't.

297
00:23:05,967 --> 00:23:07,010
Before,

298
00:23:09,012 --> 00:23:12,140
you asked how my dad injured his hand.

299
00:23:15,602 --> 00:23:16,686
It was my fault.

300
00:23:19,606 --> 00:23:23,026
My dad was cleaning
the machine at the mill.

301
00:23:26,029 --> 00:23:27,989
I accidentally turned it on.

302
00:23:32,244 --> 00:23:34,412
It's the first time I've told
anyone outside my family.

303
00:23:36,790 --> 00:23:37,916
Sir...

304
00:23:39,126 --> 00:23:40,710
Lieutenant.

305
00:23:42,546 --> 00:23:43,797
It's because

306
00:23:44,673 --> 00:23:46,133
you're my first partner and mentor.

307
00:23:55,225 --> 00:23:57,727
I, Song Hye-ri, will head home then.

308
00:24:04,734 --> 00:24:05,610
Go.

309
00:24:06,903 --> 00:24:07,904
Get home safely.

310
00:24:10,073 --> 00:24:11,616
I'll keep in touch.

311
00:24:22,502 --> 00:24:23,503
Yang-chon,

312
00:24:24,796 --> 00:24:25,839
you should go too.

313
00:24:26,089 --> 00:24:27,507
I'll see you head inside.

314
00:26:41,057 --> 00:26:42,058
Your hands are rough.

315
00:26:43,643 --> 00:26:47,647
Go back home.
I think Jang-mi will take you back now.

316
00:26:48,315 --> 00:26:50,817
I know you live here because of me.

317
00:26:51,067 --> 00:26:52,360
I'm not that great a son.

318
00:26:54,154 --> 00:26:56,156
I like the countryside.

319
00:26:58,241 --> 00:27:00,410
Do you know it's the first time
I held your hand?

320
00:27:01,870 --> 00:27:04,205
We held hands many times
when you were a kid.

321
00:27:04,331 --> 00:27:05,749
That's a lie.

322
00:27:06,374 --> 00:27:08,835
You were always drunk.
When did we hold hands?

323
00:27:09,294 --> 00:27:13,006
Did it never happen if
you don't remember it, you weirdo?

324
00:27:17,010 --> 00:27:19,346
Do you have soup? I want bean sprout soup.

325
00:27:20,680 --> 00:27:21,973
I made some already.

326
00:27:23,641 --> 00:27:25,769
We agreed on something
for the first time in 40 years.

327
00:27:26,269 --> 00:27:27,354
That's weird.

328
00:27:39,115 --> 00:27:41,326
You should do something about your leg.

329
00:27:41,826 --> 00:27:44,329
Get it looked at and treated, okay?

330
00:27:44,412 --> 00:27:46,456
Why don't you ever listen?

331
00:27:54,964 --> 00:27:56,007
JEONG-O

332
00:27:59,177 --> 00:28:00,220
Hey, it's me.

333
00:28:00,762 --> 00:28:01,763
<i>Did you sleep?</i>

334
00:28:02,055 --> 00:28:03,848
Yes. It's dark already.

335
00:28:03,932 --> 00:28:05,350
It must've been the alcohol.

336
00:28:05,433 --> 00:28:06,476
<i>Shall we meet?</i>

337
00:28:07,060 --> 00:28:09,813
Sure. Do you want a beer? I'll bring some.

338
00:28:32,043 --> 00:28:33,086
Sorry.

339
00:28:35,046 --> 00:28:36,464
Why are you always sorry?

340
00:28:39,050 --> 00:28:41,177
Before I made the decision,

341
00:28:43,847 --> 00:28:46,015
I should've at least talked to you first.

342
00:28:47,934 --> 00:28:50,145
I shouldn't have let you
hear it from Hye-ri.

343
00:28:55,233 --> 00:28:56,359
Like you said,

344
00:28:59,320 --> 00:29:02,115
although we weren't very serious,

345
00:29:04,909 --> 00:29:05,910
I...

346
00:29:08,246 --> 00:29:09,706
really like you a lot.

347
00:29:14,043 --> 00:29:16,546
I feel like I'm running away
to save my own skin.

348
00:29:20,550 --> 00:29:22,010
I feel bad about

349
00:29:23,511 --> 00:29:27,390
what I'm doing to not only you,
but to everyone in our division.

350
00:29:34,189 --> 00:29:35,398
The people here

351
00:29:36,357 --> 00:29:38,359
stayed because they like something.

352
00:29:39,360 --> 00:29:42,655
They prefer the field and
have more fun than they would

353
00:29:43,448 --> 00:29:45,450
sitting behind a desk all day.

354
00:29:47,410 --> 00:29:49,370
They weren't forced by
their sense of duty.

355
00:29:53,291 --> 00:29:54,959
A lot of bad things happen,

356
00:29:55,210 --> 00:29:58,379
but like two days ago,
we also get to save lives.

357
00:30:01,007 --> 00:30:02,926
It's wrong for you to feel bad.

358
00:30:04,511 --> 00:30:05,595
But

359
00:30:07,347 --> 00:30:08,598
I am angry.

360
00:30:14,437 --> 00:30:15,563
How come you're not asking me

361
00:30:20,193 --> 00:30:21,861
to wait for you?

362
00:30:24,781 --> 00:30:27,158
That's what upsets and angers me.

363
00:30:32,247 --> 00:30:34,791
Can I wait for you to come back?

364
00:30:37,627 --> 00:30:40,380
Some women wait while
their boyfriends serve in the army.

365
00:30:43,049 --> 00:30:44,259
I can wait.

366
00:30:47,971 --> 00:30:48,972
Jeong-o.

367
00:30:49,597 --> 00:30:53,101
How would you feel if I failed to wait

368
00:30:54,310 --> 00:30:55,979
until you come back

369
00:30:57,522 --> 00:30:59,065
and dated someone else?

370
00:31:03,027 --> 00:31:04,028
Well...

371
00:31:07,407 --> 00:31:09,033
I probably won't be able to do anything

372
00:31:12,078 --> 00:31:13,538
but I think I'd get upset.

373
00:31:24,090 --> 00:31:25,049
Really?

374
00:31:27,510 --> 00:31:28,595
Really.

375
00:31:35,643 --> 00:31:36,644
Then...

376
00:31:42,233 --> 00:31:44,110
tell me to wait for you.

377
00:32:02,211 --> 00:32:03,379
Wait for me.

378
00:32:20,521 --> 00:32:22,148
I like you too.

379
00:32:24,359 --> 00:32:26,444
It's the job that exhausts me.

380
00:32:27,737 --> 00:32:29,280
I don't dislike you.

381
00:32:32,700 --> 00:32:33,743
I'll wait for you.

382
00:32:37,080 --> 00:32:38,164
That's nice.

383
00:32:41,000 --> 00:32:42,210
To tell the truth,

384
00:32:44,420 --> 00:32:48,257
I was really afraid
you'd say you wouldn't wait.

385
00:33:01,229 --> 00:33:03,606
I was afraid you'd tell me
not to wait for you, you dummy.

386
00:33:18,413 --> 00:33:20,665
Let's have one more bottle.
Do you have alcohol?

387
00:33:21,040 --> 00:33:22,709
-No.
-I'll buy some.

388
00:33:23,292 --> 00:33:24,252
I'll come too.

389
00:33:33,302 --> 00:33:35,388
Is it easier to walk with your long legs?

390
00:33:35,805 --> 00:33:37,265
Is it hard for you?

391
00:33:37,348 --> 00:33:39,392
No, it's just hard to keep up with you.

392
00:33:40,143 --> 00:33:41,144
Let's walk in sync.

393
00:33:42,979 --> 00:33:44,063
Stand still.

394
00:33:44,397 --> 00:33:46,607
-Left foot forward.
-Left foot forward.

395
00:33:49,527 --> 00:33:50,528
You're losing it.

396
00:33:50,611 --> 00:33:52,238
You put your right foot forward.

397
00:33:52,321 --> 00:33:54,365
Just do whatever I do.

398
00:33:55,908 --> 00:33:57,076
Try again.

399
00:33:57,285 --> 00:33:58,536
Left foot forward.

400
00:33:59,078 --> 00:34:02,457
-One, two, one, two.
-One, two, one, two.

401
00:34:02,540 --> 00:34:04,167
One, two.

402
00:34:04,250 --> 00:34:06,919
One, two, one, two.

403
00:34:42,455 --> 00:34:45,333
Hey, have some water.

404
00:34:56,344 --> 00:34:58,888
Someone's house in the area
got robbed last night.

405
00:34:59,263 --> 00:35:01,474
Cops camped out in the area all night.

406
00:35:01,849 --> 00:35:04,227
There are side dishes in the fridge.

407
00:35:04,310 --> 00:35:05,561
Make sure you eat them.

408
00:35:19,575 --> 00:35:21,494
I'm going to Jeong-do's place.

409
00:35:27,333 --> 00:35:30,586
You haven't gone outside at all
since you retired.

410
00:35:30,670 --> 00:35:31,879
You just watch TV all day.

411
00:35:32,755 --> 00:35:34,841
Aren't you going to start
looking for a job?

412
00:35:36,884 --> 00:35:38,511
No, I won't.

413
00:35:40,513 --> 00:35:41,597
All right, take it easy.

414
00:35:41,681 --> 00:35:44,684
You're not a machine.
You've worked all your life.

415
00:35:45,810 --> 00:35:46,894
Get some rest.

416
00:35:53,693 --> 00:35:56,195
MY LAST ROOKIE

417
00:36:06,414 --> 00:36:07,665
Go. Next.

418
00:36:09,458 --> 00:36:10,293
Hey, Yang-chon.

419
00:36:10,877 --> 00:36:11,836
Come to my office after.

420
00:36:11,919 --> 00:36:13,796
-Yes, sir.
-One blank, three live. All good.

421
00:36:14,380 --> 00:36:15,464
It's probably about Jeong-o.

422
00:36:15,673 --> 00:36:17,175
She just asked to meet with Chief Ki.

423
00:36:22,638 --> 00:36:24,390
One blank, three live. All good.

424
00:36:24,557 --> 00:36:25,600
Next.

425
00:36:29,896 --> 00:36:30,938
Hey.

426
00:36:31,606 --> 00:36:33,524
Probationary officers
can't request a leave.

427
00:36:33,858 --> 00:36:35,735
The workload here can be overwhelming,

428
00:36:35,818 --> 00:36:37,695
so I understand how hard it must be.

429
00:36:43,743 --> 00:36:44,744
Hey, Han Jeong-o.

430
00:36:47,663 --> 00:36:48,497
Are you sick?

431
00:36:50,416 --> 00:36:51,250
No, sir.

432
00:36:51,834 --> 00:36:53,920
Then what is it? Is your mother ill?

433
00:36:55,338 --> 00:36:56,172
No, sir.

434
00:36:56,964 --> 00:36:59,842
You're not even ill.
What rookie requests a leave

435
00:36:59,926 --> 00:37:02,762
in less than a year
after joining the force?

436
00:37:04,472 --> 00:37:05,890
But it's not against the rules.

437
00:37:06,891 --> 00:37:08,476
Unbelievable.

438
00:37:09,602 --> 00:37:12,480
It's not against the rules,
but it's disrespectful.

439
00:37:12,980 --> 00:37:16,817
Do you think that you can do
whatever you want to do

440
00:37:16,901 --> 00:37:17,944
once you join the force?

441
00:37:19,820 --> 00:37:21,280
Just let her do it.

442
00:37:21,948 --> 00:37:23,616
What the hell are you talking about?

443
00:37:25,326 --> 00:37:27,828
Our precinct is
so short-staffed at the moment.

444
00:37:28,955 --> 00:37:31,582
You know how big
Lieutenant Lee's absence is.

445
00:37:33,834 --> 00:37:37,255
Hana, Myeongu, and Mapo Divisions
all have about five to six young officers

446
00:37:37,880 --> 00:37:39,548
who requested

447
00:37:39,924 --> 00:37:42,760
transfers to easier precincts

448
00:37:42,927 --> 00:37:45,888
after Captain Kang's incident.

449
00:37:46,514 --> 00:37:48,724
They're scared to work
in this crime-ridden area.

450
00:37:49,308 --> 00:37:51,227
It's affecting
Team Two, Three, and Four as well.

451
00:37:52,019 --> 00:37:53,354
Jeong-o,

452
00:37:54,772 --> 00:37:56,357
this division needs

453
00:37:56,899 --> 00:37:58,234
competent officers like you.

454
00:38:05,908 --> 00:38:07,618
Chief Ki, I'd like to talk to you about--

455
00:38:07,702 --> 00:38:09,120
About what?

456
00:38:13,749 --> 00:38:15,459
Never mind. We can talk another time.

457
00:38:24,427 --> 00:38:27,471
Did you tell him that you want
to transfer to the countryside?

458
00:38:28,055 --> 00:38:28,931
No, I couldn't.

459
00:38:29,598 --> 00:38:32,393
Gosh, come on. Just stay here with me.

460
00:38:32,893 --> 00:38:34,645
-Let's go on patrol.
-Yes, sir.

461
00:38:37,690 --> 00:38:39,567
Hey, is he requesting a transfer?

462
00:38:41,610 --> 00:38:42,945
No, I'm not sure, sir.

463
00:38:51,037 --> 00:38:52,038
Jeong-o.

464
00:38:52,747 --> 00:38:53,831
I'm fully aware

465
00:38:55,124 --> 00:38:57,668
of how challenging
working at this division can be.

466
00:38:58,252 --> 00:38:59,295
But if you wish

467
00:39:00,421 --> 00:39:02,882
to move up the ladder
and become a higher-up

468
00:39:04,383 --> 00:39:05,801
in this organization down the road,

469
00:39:06,886 --> 00:39:08,637
you must know
what happens out in the field

470
00:39:10,598 --> 00:39:12,475
in order to become a really good cop.

471
00:39:13,100 --> 00:39:14,435
The police force can't exist

472
00:39:14,810 --> 00:39:15,978
without patrol divisions.

473
00:39:17,146 --> 00:39:20,649
Chief Ki, stop trying
to meddle in someone else's life.

474
00:39:22,693 --> 00:39:24,653
The work at our division
is exceptionally hard,

475
00:39:24,820 --> 00:39:28,157
so only those who want to work here
should stay.

476
00:39:31,744 --> 00:39:32,661
And go home already.

477
00:39:33,662 --> 00:39:36,415
You said you'd only stay late on the days
when you're on night duty.

478
00:39:48,552 --> 00:39:49,637
Hey, Jeong-o.

479
00:39:52,515 --> 00:39:55,726
If all competent cops like you run away
because they don't want to work here,

480
00:39:58,521 --> 00:39:59,939
what will happen to this precinct?

481
00:40:08,781 --> 00:40:09,949
I'm sorry, sir.

482
00:40:11,242 --> 00:40:13,160
I can't put the safety of the citizens

483
00:40:14,537 --> 00:40:17,123
before my own sake like you
and Chief Ki do

484
00:40:18,791 --> 00:40:21,252
because I don't have a sense of duty.

485
00:40:22,628 --> 00:40:24,547
You don't need

486
00:40:24,922 --> 00:40:26,173
such a sense of duty.

487
00:40:28,801 --> 00:40:30,678
Put others before yourself?

488
00:40:31,804 --> 00:40:33,764
No one can force anyone to do that.

489
00:40:40,688 --> 00:40:41,897
Frankly, I don't quite

490
00:40:42,106 --> 00:40:43,941
understand the sense of duty either.

491
00:40:44,650 --> 00:40:45,860
Hence, I've arrived at

492
00:40:46,569 --> 00:40:49,113
a simple conclusion that
I should at least do what I get paid for.

493
00:40:50,865 --> 00:40:52,825
Even though I don't understand
the sense of duty,

494
00:40:53,033 --> 00:40:55,870
I should at least have a conscience
as a human being.

495
00:40:57,872 --> 00:40:59,457
You have that too.

496
00:41:01,876 --> 00:41:03,586
If someone is dying,

497
00:41:03,878 --> 00:41:05,754
you'll do your best
to save that person's life.

498
00:41:06,630 --> 00:41:08,132
You'll get angry when you see a perp,

499
00:41:08,632 --> 00:41:10,009
and you'll catch them if you can.

500
00:41:10,801 --> 00:41:12,011
You won't commit corrupt deeds,

501
00:41:12,344 --> 00:41:14,763
and you'll obey the laws.
You won't take kickbacks,

502
00:41:15,306 --> 00:41:17,224
and you'll help others when you can.

503
00:41:17,933 --> 00:41:19,727
You'll do those things wherever you go,

504
00:41:20,352 --> 00:41:23,731
just like what you've been doing here.
Wherever you go.

505
00:41:24,940 --> 00:41:26,066
Am I wrong?

506
00:41:28,152 --> 00:41:29,487
No, I will.

507
00:41:33,199 --> 00:41:34,617
Then what's the problem?

508
00:41:39,663 --> 00:41:40,706
Just

509
00:41:41,290 --> 00:41:43,250
make sure you study as hard as you can,

510
00:41:43,918 --> 00:41:45,753
so you can become a high-ranking officer

511
00:41:47,713 --> 00:41:49,173
and change the world.

512
00:41:51,175 --> 00:41:52,760
I can't do it because I'm not smart,

513
00:41:53,594 --> 00:41:54,845
but I think you'll be able to.

514
00:42:00,851 --> 00:42:02,811
Oh, what did Sang-su say about it?

515
00:42:04,813 --> 00:42:06,148
He said he'll wait for me.

516
00:42:07,942 --> 00:42:08,901
He's cute.

517
00:42:09,318 --> 00:42:11,153
